					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I found this ROM I made a while back for testing the RAM startup/reset state on my NES. Sharing it in case anybody would find it useful.<br /><br />It clobbers the low 3 bytes of ZP, and also the top couple of bytes of the stack page, but otherwise just shows RAM on the screen, and you can press up/down to browse the 8 pages. (B and A fill the page with ascending or descending values, was used to test reset state.)<br /><br />Edit: I think jroatch's <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=22&amp;t=11520" class="postlink">coredump ROM</a> is better than this, though, seems to manage not to clobber any bytes at all. Might as well use that instead.</div>

					
